From: GloriousEggroll <gloriouseggroll@proton.me>
Date: Sun, 28 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winedmo: fill codec-aligned video output padding

Riddle Joker's H.264 videos decode as 1920x1080 frames, but the stream
output type is advertised as codec-aligned 1920x1088 NV12. Returning only
the visible 1080p byte count causes the MF sample copier to update only
the visible rows while leaving the D3D surface padding stale, which shows
up as a green bar at the bottom of the video.

When the codec-aligned dimensions are only small padding over the decoded
frame, return and copy the padded output size. The NV12 copy path already
initializes the padded area to neutral black/chroma, and real dynamic size
changes such as Yakuza 5's 1080p-to-720p startup videos are unaffected
because they are not a small padding delta.
---
 dlls/winedmo/unix_transform.c | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/dlls/winedmo/unix_transform.c b/dlls/winedmo/unix_transform.c
--- a/dlls/winedmo/unix_transform.c
+++ b/dlls/winedmo/unix_transform.c
@@ -1449,6 +1449,14 @@ NTSTATUS transform_get_output( void *arg )
         UINT32 required = video_frame_size( out_fmt, out_width, out_height );
         NTSTATUS st;
 
+        if (t->avctx && t->avctx->coded_width >= out_width && t->avctx->coded_height >= out_height
+                && t->avctx->coded_width - out_width < 16 && t->avctx->coded_height - out_height < 16)
+        {
+            out_width = t->avctx->coded_width;
+            out_height = t->avctx->coded_height;
+            required = video_frame_size( out_fmt, out_width, out_height );
+        }
+
         if (capacity < required)
         {
             params->size = required;
-- 
